  "metadata": {
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Adopting best practices for privacy and user preferences"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To protect user privacy, the system handles camera and sensor inputs",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "without passing the information to apps directly. Instead, the system",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "enables your app to seamlessly interact with a user’s surroundings",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and to automatically receive input from the user. For example, the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "system handles the eye- and hand-position data needed to detect",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "interactions with your app’s content. Similarly, the system provides",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "a way to automatically alter a view’s appearance when someone looks at it,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "without your app ever knowing what the user is looking at.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In the few cases where you actually need access to hand position or",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "information about the user’s surroundings, the system requires you",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to obtain authorization from the user first.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "tracking-authorization.png",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "It’s your responsibility to protect any data your app",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "collects, and to use it in responsible and privacy-preserving ways.",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Don’t ask for data that you don’t need, be transparent about how",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "you use the data you acquire, and respect the choices of the person",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "whose data it is.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Important",
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For information about how to specify the privacy data your app uses,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/BundleResources/describing-data-use-in-privacy-manifests",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For general information about privacy, see",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/UIKit/protecting-the-user-s-privacy",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Adopt-the-system-provided-input-mechanisms",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Adopt the system-provided input mechanisms",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "On Apple Vision Pro, people use their eyes and hands to interact with the items",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "they see in front of them. Where they look determines where the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "system applies focus, and a tap gesture with either hand generates",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "a touch event on that focused item. The system can also detect when",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "someone’s fingers interact with virtual items in the person’s field",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "of vision. When you adopt the standard UIKit and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "SwiftUI event-handling mechanisms, you get all of these interactions",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "automatically.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For most apps, the system-provided gesture recognizers are sufficient",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "for responding to interactions. Although you can get the position of",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "someone’s hands with ARKit, doing so isn’t necessary for most apps.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Collect hand-position data only when the system doesn’t offer what",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you need. For example, you might use hand-position data to attach 3D",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "content to the person’s hands. Some other things to remember about",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "hand-position data:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "People can deny your request for access to hand-position data. Be prepared to handle situations where the data isn’t available.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "You must present an immersive space to access hand data. When you open an immersive space, the system hides other apps.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For information about how to handle the standard-system events, see",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/SwiftUI",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/UIKit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " documentation.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Provide-clear-messaging-around-privacy-sensitive-features",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Provide clear messaging around privacy-sensitive features",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The following ARKit features require you to provide a usage description",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "string in your app’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Info.plist",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " file:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "World-tracking data",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Hand-tracking data",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Other privacy-sensitive technologies in visionOS also require you to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "supply usage description strings. For example, you provide usage",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "descriptions for the Core Location features you adopt. These strings",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "communicate why your app needs the data, and how you plan to use the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "data to help the person using your app. The first time you request",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "authorization to use the technology, the system prompts the person",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to grant or deny access to your app. The system includes your",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "usage-description string in the dialog it displays.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For information about requesting access to ARKit data, see",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For guidance on how to craft good messages around privacy-friendly",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "features, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/design/Human-Interface-Guidelines/privacy",
              "isActive": true,
              "overridingTitle": "Human Interface Guidelines",
              "overridingTitleInlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Human Interface Guidelines",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
